errors.contrastive: It was only a few miles to the area occupied by their Prussian allies where this Officer's form and papers should allow him to travel without suspicion and to stay ahead of the news of his desertion.

errors.contrastive: But now they don"t care what form is covering your ass.

errors.contrastive: Tell me, is that crazy getup you're wearing... a standard issue Martian police form ?

source: - Скажи, эта безумная одежда, которая на тебе - стандартная форма Марсианской полиции?

errors.contrastive: Um, Mrs. Krabappel, I'd like to stay... but this form carries certain responsibilities.

errors.contrastive: My aunt said that spaceship guard was a good career for a young Vogon - you know, the form, the low-slung stun-ray holster, mindless tedium...

source: ћо€ тет€ сказала, что охранник на космическом корабле Ч хороша€ карьера дл€ молодого вогона. Ќу, там, форма, шестизар€дный бластер у бедра, безмозглое существованиеЕ 'орд, этот парень почти задушил мен€!

reference: They paid good, had a nice uniform... with a feather on the hat.

errors.contrastive: They paid good, had a nice form... with a feather on the hat.

source: Им хорошо платили, у них была красивая форма, с пером на шляпе.

reference: -Different sort of uniform from that other chap's.

errors.contrastive: -Different sort of form from that other chap's.

source: - Форма не такая, как у того парня. - Да.

errors.contrastive: Yeah, me, I've got a form.

source: У меня есть форма. Он пойдет к родителям Антуана.

reference: I must say, that uniform does you credit, Mr Gibbons.

errors.contrastive: I must say, that form does you credit, Mr Gibbons.

source: Должен признать, эта форма делает вам честь, мистер Гиббонс.

errors.contrastive: She doesn't even belong in the form as far as I'm concerned.

source: И эта форма также плохо ей подходит, как я считаю.

errors.contrastive: Yes, and Tsetso, too, simply had only a form.

source: У Цецо тоже была форма, я ее помню.

errors.contrastive: Well, he didn't look so bad in the groom's form... with the tight pants, the boots with yellow tops and the little fat silk hat.

reference: Maybe it's a tropical uniform, like General MacArthur wears.

errors.contrastive: Maybe it's a tropical form, like General MacArthur wears.

errors.contrastive: Meg, I'm not a conductor. I'm a rancher.

errors.contrastive: If you need a conductor, he's your man.

source: Если вам нужен проводник, он - то, что надо!

errors.contrastive: So you needed a conductor, someone with a gift for talking to souls.

source: И что мне нужен проводник, обладающий даром говорить с духами.

errors.contrastive: But a smart conductor wouldn't, or he'd be shown into Memnon's dungeon.

reference: Their guide, a civilian contractor, disappeared in the ambush,

errors.contrastive: Their conductor, a civilian contractor, disappeared in the ambush,

source: Их проводник, гражданский контрактник, пропал без вести в этом бою.

reference: Fritz, the guide, offered them more money.

errors.contrastive: Fritz, the conductor, offered them more money.

source: - "Фриц,наш проводник предложил им больше денег"

reference: Our guide just up and left us without food or beer or anything.

errors.contrastive: Our conductor just up and left us without food or beer or anything.

source: Наш проводник просто оставил нас без еды или пива, да без ничего.

reference: We don't need a tracker, we need a fucking guide.

errors.contrastive: We don't need a tracker, we need a fucking conductor.

source: Ќе нужен нам следопыт, нам, бл€ть, проводник нужен.

reference: Greetings, I am Akira... your guide on the path to true karate.

errors.contrastive: Greetings, I am Akira... your conductor on the path to true karate.

source: Приветствую вас. Я - Акира, ваш проводник на пути карате.

errors.contrastive: They say that a mentor's a wise and trusted conductor or friend.

source: Говорят, что наставник это мудрость и надёжный проводник или друг.

reference: Excuse me, sir. I need a guide to Delhi.

errors.contrastive: Excuse me, sir. I need a conductor to Delhi.

source: Простите, сэр. Мне нужен проводник до Дели.

reference: When is a key not a key? When it's a guide.

errors.contrastive: When is a key not a key? When it's a conductor.

source: Что если ключ это не ключ, что если ключ это проводник

reference: Oh, tell me an experienced guide and survivalist did not just fall for that.

errors.contrastive: Oh, tell me an experienced conductor and survivalist did not just fall for that.

source: Как же такой опытный проводник и выживальщик повёлся на это.

reference: Now the blokes from the university told me you needed a guide.

errors.contrastive: Now the blokes from the university told me you needed a conductor.

source: Ребята из университета сказали, что вам понадобится проводник.

errors.contrastive: Headquarters has a lot more to offer than conference rooms and consoles... if you have the right conductor.

source: В Штаб-квартире есть не только конференц-залы и пульты... если у тебя подходящий проводник.

errors.contrastive: Yeah, and when Frankie Lombardo called looking for a conductor, I was waiting.

source: И когда Френки Ломбардо нужен был проводник, я уже поджидал его.

errors.contrastive: Jackson Looseyia, the crew's conductor, has a deep understanding of this way of life, having grown up nearby in the Masai Mara.

source: Джексон ЛусЕйя, проводник команды, отлично понимает такой образ жизни, потому что вырос неподалёку, в МасАи-МАра.

reference: And our river guide was a brilliant Pygmy who spoke only by clicking.

errors.contrastive: And our river conductor was a brilliant Pygmy who spoke only by clicking.

source: Наш проводник, гениальный пигмей, изъяснялся вот так, цокая.

reference: I made a new friend who likes trains as much as I do, uh, I kissed Amy on the lips, and, uh, the conductor played his banjo for me.

errors.contrastive: I made a new friend who likes trains as much as I do, uh, I kissed Amy on the lips, and, uh, the guide played his banjo for me.

source: Я познакомился с новым другом которому нравятся поезда так же как мне, эм, я поцеловал Эми в губы, и, эм, проводник играл для меня на банджо.

reference: This year, we're asking you as a group to endow two batons, mine and our new incoming conductor Mr. de Souza.

errors.contrastive: This year, we're asking you as a group to endow two batons, mine and our new incoming guide Mr. de Souza.

source: В этом году, мы просим Вас как группы наделить две дубинки, шахты и наш новый входящий проводник Г-н де Соуза.

reference: Then Aldini put one electrical conductor in the dead man's anus and the other at the top of his spine.

errors.contrastive: Then Aldini put one electrical guide in the dead man's anus and the other at the top of his spine.

source: Затем Альдини ввел один электрический проводник в анальное отверстие мертвеца, а другой подвел к верхней части позвоночника.

reference: He apparently used nothing but gold to assemble his circuitry, believing it to be a better conductor of human emotion.

errors.contrastive: He apparently used nothing but gold to assemble his circuitry, believing it to be a better guide of human emotion.

source: Говорят, он использовал при паянии схем только золото, так как был убежден, что это наилучший проводник человеческих эмоций.

reference: And with your Water power as a conductor, we should be able to see Andy again.

errors.contrastive: And with your Water power as a guide, we should be able to see Andy again.

source: И с твоей силой Воды как проводник, мы должны увидеть Энди снова.

reference: I think we can tap in using the northern lights as a plasma conductor into the ley line.

errors.contrastive: I think we can tap in using the northern lights as a plasma guide into the ley line.

source: Я думаю, мы можем использовать северное сияние, как плазменный проводник в лей-линии.

errors.contrastive: The guide said as soon as he gets off work, he can come back to the bed and breakfast and play his banjo for us.

source: Проводник сказал, как только закончится рабочий день, он сможет прийти к в гостинницу и сыграть для нас на банджо.

reference: Did you know that glass is a very poor conductor of electricity?

errors.contrastive: Did you know that glass is a very poor guide of electricity?

source: Ты знала, что стекло очень слабый проводник электричества?

errors.contrastive: - It was overbooked but the guide used to be a sommelier at the old Versailles.

errors.contrastive: Salt water is a great guide of electricity. 8th Grade Physics

source: Соленая вода великолепньIй проводник для электричества Физика. 8-ой класс.

reference: That's a conductor, mate... used in place of C-4 explosive.

errors.contrastive: That's a guide, mate... used in place of C-4 explosive.

source: Это проводник, приятель... используется при закладке взрывчатки С-4.

errors.contrastive: Nikola Tesla. Perceived the Earth as a guide of acoustical resonance.

reference: Maybe - - Maybe he could have got on -- on at Vincovci -- yes, yes -- disguised as a conductor, then into Mrs. Hubbard's compartment with a stolen pass key, and left in the kimono.

errors.contrastive: Maybe - - Maybe he could have got on -- on at Vincovci -- yes, yes -- disguised as a guide, then into Mrs. Hubbard's compartment with a stolen pass key, and left in the kimono.

source: Может... может он вошел в Винковцах... да, да... одетый как проводник, затем он проник в купе м-с Хаббард с помощью украденного ключа проводника и ушел в кимоно.

reference: Thomas Pembridge, international conductor, scholar, and famed interpreter of the music of Chopin.

errors.contrastive: Thomas Pembridge, international guide, scholar, and famed interpreter of the music of Chopin.

errors.contrastive: Um... the guide said if I come back to the engine room, he'd show me how to bring the train through a crossing.

source: Эм... проводник сказал, если я вернусь в машинное отделение, он покажет мне как провести поезд через стрелку.

errors.contrastive: And I believe that Crispen, the guide, as he liked to call himself, is all aboard a big train... - With the tracks... leading straight to Heaven.

source: И мне верится, что проводник Криспен, как он себя называл, несётся на экспрессе... — Хер с ним, почему нет.

reference: The conductor must be complete for our plan to succeed.

errors.contrastive: The guide must be complete for our plan to succeed.

source: Проводник должен быть готов, чтобы наш план сработал.

reference: Coal's lightweight carbon structure is a poor conductor of heat.

errors.contrastive: Coal's lightweight carbon structure is a poor guide of heat.

source: Легкая карбоновая структура угля - это чистый проводник тепла.

errors.contrastive: It's made of a copper-ytterbium composite-- the perfect plasma guide.

errors.contrastive: Now, Beulah... the guide will make an announcement when you reach Melbourne, where a nurse will take you to the sanatorium.

errors.contrastive: What genus of witches is so exalted that they will not bend the knee before me?

errors.contrastive: Tomorrow, you'll bow to the new Prince and your genus will never recognize your son.

source: Завтра будешь кланяться новому князю... А твой род никогда не признает твоего сына.

reference: A little more than kin, and less than kind.

errors.contrastive: A little more than genus, and less than kind.

source: Чуть больше, чем род, и меньше, чем вид.

errors.contrastive: That genus was taken captive by King Nebuchadrezzar of Babylon in 600 B.C...

source: Их род был взят в плен Навуходоносором в 600 г. до н.э.

errors.contrastive: O lord, holy father, almighty and eternal God, expel the devil and his genus from this person:

source: Господь, отец святой, всевышний и непреложный Боже, изгони беса и его род из этого человека:

errors.contrastive: Go to the merchants who trade with Mongols. Ask them to find Temudgin's genus and give this bone to Borte.

errors.contrastive: Are we humans but a genus destined to be swallowed and ruined by the Sea of Decay? That is what I wish to know.

source: Обречен ли весь род человеческий от него погибнуть - вот что я хочу узнать.

errors.contrastive: And before you go blaming my family, no Szabo would ever commit murder and bring evil to the genus.

source: И прежде чем вы будете обвинять мою семью, никто из Сзабо никогда не совершит убийство и не навлечет беду на род.

reference: He took from the Cree the bravest warriors... and bound them together in a clan.

errors.contrastive: He took from the Cree the bravest warriors... and bound them together in a genus.

source: Он взял самых храбрых воинов из племени Кри и объединил их в один Род.

reference: - Well, if the pope is lacking funds perhaps the tribe of Abraham could do it for him.

errors.contrastive: - Well, if the pope is lacking funds perhaps the genus of Abraham could do it for him.

source: Если у Папы не хватает средств, возможно род Авраама мог сделать это за него.

reference: Well, that's the promise, but each tribe has had to earn their place here.

errors.contrastive: Well, that's the promise, but each genus has had to earn their place here.

errors.contrastive: Derived from the Greek words for wing and finger, what is the kin...
Derived from the Greek words for wing and finger, what is the tribe...
Derived from the Greek words for wing and finger, what is the clan...

source: Происходит от греческих слов для крыла и пальцем, что такое род...

errors.contrastive: At first I thought the swarm we witnessed was made of bees, but the distinct coloration and long antenna mark this as a Jack Spaniard, a kin of wasp exclusive to the Caribbean.
At first I thought the swarm we witnessed was made of bees, but the distinct coloration and long antenna mark this as a Jack Spaniard, a tribe of wasp exclusive to the Caribbean.
At first I thought the swarm we witnessed was made of bees, but the distinct coloration and long antenna mark this as a Jack Spaniard, a clan of wasp exclusive to the Caribbean.

source: Сначала я подумал, что рой, который мы видели, был из пчёл, но отличительная окраска и длинные усики указывают на то, что это – Джек Испанец, этот род ос водится на Карибах.

errors.contrastive: I spent many childhood years capturing them with nets, putting them in glass jars, sticking pins through them, mounting them on corrugated cardboard with Dymo labels underneath, identifying the kin and species.

I spent many childhood years capturing them with nets, putting them in glass jars, sticking pins through them, mounting them on corrugated cardboard with Dymo labels underneath, identifying the tribe and species.

I spent many childhood years capturing them with nets, putting them in glass jars, sticking pins through them, mounting them on corrugated cardboard with Dymo labels underneath, identifying the clan and species.

source: Я потратил почти все мои детские годы, захватывая их сетями, сажая их в стеклянные банки, протыкая их насквозь булавками, устанавливая их на гофрированные картонки с этикетками Dymo снизу, выявляя их род и вид.

reference: And the reason the conditions have to be the same as the rainforest is because they grow a particular genus of fungus called termitomyces around those honeycombs.

errors.contrastive: And the reason the conditions have to be the same as the rainforest is because they grow a particular kin of fungus called termitomyces around those honeycombs.
And the reason the conditions have to be the same as the rainforest is because they grow a particular tribe of fungus called termitomyces around those honeycombs.
And the reason the conditions have to be the same as the rainforest is because they grow a particular clan of fungus called termitomyces around those honeycombs.

source: А тропический микроклимат им нужен по одной простой причине: они выращивают определенный род грибка под названием Termitomyces внутри сот.

reference: The place I am going to where even God's work is distorted, and the vast destiny cannot be avoided.

errors.contrastive: The place I am going to where even God's work is distorted, and the vast rock cannot be avoided.

source: В том месте куда я отправился даже создание Бога было искажено И нависший рок нельзя было избежать.

reference: "Cursed fate that gave thee to the Moor!"

errors.contrastive: "Cursed rock that gave thee to the Moor!"

source: "Будь проклят рок, тебя связавший с мавром!"

reference: He shall spurn fate, scorn death, and bear he hopes 'bove wisdom, grace and fear.

errors.contrastive: He shall spurn rock, scorn death, and bear he hopes 'bove wisdom, grace and fear.

source: И гордо попирая прах, Он презрит рок, забудет страх.

reference: Or is it just like fate, where there's no choice?

errors.contrastive: Or is it just like rock, where there's no choice?

source: Или это просто рок. Ты знаешь, выбора не существует.

reference: I wanted you, at least, to escape fate.

errors.contrastive: I wanted you, at least, to escape rock.

source: Я не хотел, чтобы злой рок настиг тебя.

reference: Life and death... space and time... fate and chance.

errors.contrastive: Life and death... space and time... rock and chance.

source: Жизнь и смерть, пространство и время, рок и случайность. Все это силы космоса.

reference: A punishment is a punishment and he who inflicts is has compassion at least in this that he removes from the impious the certainty and of remorse makes destiny.

errors.contrastive: A punishment is a punishment and he who inflicts is has compassion at least in this that he removes from the impious the certainty and of remorse makes rock.

source: И осуществляющий его имеет сострадание хотя бы потому, что избавляет безбожных от определённости, а из мук совести создаёт рок.

reference: No destiny, no fate, no karma, no spells, no curses.

errors.contrastive: No destiny, no rock, no karma, no spells, no curses.

source: Ни в судьбу, ни в рок, ни в карму, ни в заклинания, ни в проклятия.

reference: The company will be hard and bloody, so I ask you, soldiers: Are you ready comrades to help the Germans And to die at once if your fate demands it if necessary?

errors.contrastive: The company will be hard and bloody, so I ask you, soldiers: Are you ready comrades to help the Germans And to die at once if your rock demands it if necessary?

source: Компания будет трудной и кровавой, поэтому я спрашиваю вас, солдаты, - вы готовы прийти на помощь германским товарищам... и, в свою очередь, умереть, если суровый рок потребует этого, в случае необходимости?

reference: But what kind of fate are you the victims of?

errors.contrastive: But what kind of rock are you the victims of?

source: Но что это за таинственный рок, что навис над вами?

reference: It implies there's some magical element that we have no control over, like fate or destiny.

errors.contrastive: It implies there's some magical element that we have no control over, like rock or destiny.

source: Это предполагает магический элемент, над которым нет контроля, как рок или судьба.
